		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="430" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">Generally speaking, since 1971 there [2] (be) a marked upward trend in the numbers of people living alone among the under 65s and this trend [3] (be) most pronounced for men. In 1971 only about 3.5 per cent of households [4] (consist) of one man living alone. By 2001 this figure [5] (shoot up) to over 10 per cent. It is predicted that by 2021 the proportion [6] (reach) almost 14 per cent of all households.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
